**DOC-06  ·  UI/UX Design System ****&**** Wireframes — v1.1**

Version 1.0  ·  Confidential  ·  June 2026

# **IMPORTANT — Figma design replaceability**

| **This document defines structure, spacing, interaction, and proposed default tokens. It is not a final visual design.** When Figma designs are delivered, they supersede all visual decisions in this document: Color palette — Figma overrides DOC-06 colors. The semantic token names remain valid; values update to Figma's choices. Typography — Figma overrides typeface, weights, and scale. The type style names (display-dish, label-slot, etc.) remain valid. Component aesthetics — Figma overrides corner radii, shadows, imagery treatment, iconography. Illustrations and imagery — Figma governs completely. **What Figma does NOT override:** Structural wireframes — screen zone hierarchy, layout, information density. These remain authoritative. Gesture specification — swipe-reveal, tap targets, action bar layout. Structural, not visual. Spacing system — 4px base unit and the 9 spacing tokens. Figma should align to these or propose explicit overrides. Screen inventory and navigation model — screen IDs, entry/exit points, and states defined in DOC-05. Accessibility requirements — WCAG touch targets, contrast ratios, reduced-motion support. |
| --- |

# **CHANGE NOTICE — v1.0 → v1.1**

| **Changes in v1.1:** Figma replaceability note added (see section above) — design tokens are proposals until Figma signs off C-03 (Gesture Zones) replaced by C-03 (Swipe-Reveal Action Buttons) — long-press fully removed C-11 (Migration Duration Slider) added — new onboarding component for OB-03 C-07 (OB-07 dish preference swipe) updated — now left/right card swipe with visible action buttons from prototype H-01 wireframe updated — action bar now shows swap icon explicitly; left swipe = action reveal OB-00 wireframe added — conversational intro screen OB-08b wireframe added — single-day plan preview |
| --- |

# **01  Design philosophy — three principles (unchanged)**

| **Principle** | **What it means** | **What it rules out** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Warm and grounded** | The app lives in a kitchen at 7 AM. It should feel like a confident friend who knows your family's food — not a health dashboard or a tech product. | Clinical white backgrounds. Cold blue accents. Icon-heavy interfaces. Dense data tables on the home screen. |
| **Card is the product** | Every feature exists to serve one interaction: the user seeing the right meal card at the right moment. The home screen is three cards. | Dashboards. Menus buried in navigation. Information architecture that obscures the plan. |
| **Gestures as language** | Swipe, lock, swap, never — these are physical actions mapping to emotional states. Every action has a visible entry point. No hidden gestures. | Long-press. Shake-to-undo. Any gesture with no visual affordance. |

# **02  Brand personality — three adjectives (unchanged)**

**Warm. Confident. Grounded. **These adjectives govern every visual decision until Figma files arrive.

| **Figma note: **The visual expression of these adjectives is open for Figma to interpret. The adjectives themselves are non-negotiable product requirements. |
| --- |

# **03  Color system — proposed defaults (Figma may override)**

| **Status: proposed. **These are the default colors for development until Figma delivers. Figma overrides take effect immediately when delivered. The semantic token names remain unchanged. |
| --- |

| **Token** | **Proposed hex** | **Usage rule** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **color.background.primary** | #FAFAF5 (Cream) | App background — warm, not white. Makes food photography look appetising. |
| **color.background.surface** | #FFFFFF (White) | Card surfaces only. Lifts above cream background. |
| **color.background.secondary** | #F0EDE6 (Stone) | Inputs, secondary panels, unselected filter chips. |
| **color.brand.primary** | #1A5C38 (Forest Green) | Primary CTAs, tab bar active, section headers, lock state. |
| **color.brand.accent** | #E8910A (Saffron) | SPARINGLY: swap icon on first use, AI confidence dot, plan preview CTA, onboarding progress indicator. |
| **color.text.primary** | #1C1C1E (Charcoal) | All headings and body text. |
| **color.text.secondary** | #6B6B6B (Stone Gray) | Metadata, labels, descriptions, timestamps. |
| **color.gesture.reveal.nottoday** | #F59E0B (Amber) | Not Today swipe-reveal button background. |
| **color.gesture.reveal.never** | #E53935 (Red) | Never swipe-reveal button background. |
| **color.gesture.lock** | #1A5C38 (Green) | Lock state indicator on locked cards. |
| **color.feedback.success** | #1D9E75 | Success toasts, check states. |
| **color.feedback.error** | #DC3545 | Error states only. |

# **04  Typography — proposed defaults (Figma may override)**

| **Proposed typeface: **Plus Jakarta Sans via expo-google-fonts. Figma may specify a different typeface — the type style names (display-dish, label-slot, etc.) are the stable contract, not the specific font family. |
| --- |

| **Style name** | **Size** | **Weight** | **Used for** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **display-dish** | 24px | SemiBold 600 | Dish name on meal card — the most important text in the app |
| **display-section** | 20px | Bold 700 | Day header, screen titles |
| **heading-1** | 18px | SemiBold 600 | Card section titles, modal headers |
| **heading-2** | 16px | SemiBold 600 | Sub-section titles, list headers |
| **body-large** | 16px | Regular 400 | Primary body copy, ingredient list |
| **body-medium** | 14px | Regular 400 | Secondary descriptions |
| **label-slot** | 11px · 1px tracking | Medium 500 · ALL CAPS | BREAKFAST / LUNCH / DINNER slot labels |
| **label-cuisine** | 11px · 0.5px tracking | Medium 500 · ALL CAPS | Cuisine tag on card |
| **meta-data** | 12px | Regular 400 | Cook time, calories, timestamps |
| **button-primary** | 16px | SemiBold 600 | Primary buttons |
| **caption** | 11px · 0.2px tracking | Regular 400 | Legal, footnotes, version |

